resource.name: code
resource.description:
Multiple Resources: 

* [AllergyIntolerance](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/allergyintolerance.html): Code that identifies the allergy or intolerance
* [Condition](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/condition.html): Code for the condition
* [DeviceRequest](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/devicerequest.html): Code for what is being requested/ordered
* [DiagnosticReport](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/diagnosticreport.html): The code for the report, as opposed to codes for the atomic results, which are the names on the observation resource referred to from the result
* [FamilyMemberHistory](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/familymemberhistory.html): A search by a condition code
* [List](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/list.html): What the purpose of this list is
* [Medication](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/medication.html): Returns medications for a specific code
* [MedicationAdministration](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/medicationadministration.html): Return administrations of this medication code
* [MedicationDispense](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/medicationdispense.html): Returns dispenses of this medicine code
* [MedicationRequest](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/medicationrequest.html): Return prescriptions of this medication code
* [MedicationStatement](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/medicationstatement.html): Return statements of this medication code
* [Observation](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/observation.html): The code of the observation type
* [Procedure](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/procedure.html): A code to identify a  procedure
* [ServiceRequest](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/servicerequest.html): What is being requested/ordered

resource.name: date
resource.description:
Multiple Resources: 

* [AllergyIntolerance](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/allergyintolerance.html): Date first version of the resource instance was recorded
* [CarePlan](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/careplan.html): Time period plan covers
* [CareTeam](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/careteam.html): Time period team covers
* [ClinicalImpression](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/clinicalimpression.html): When the assessment was documented
* [Composition](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/composition.html): Composition editing time
* [Consent](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/consent.html): When this Consent was created or indexed
* [DiagnosticReport](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/diagnosticreport.html): The clinically relevant time of the report
* [Encounter](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/encounter.html): A date within the period the Encounter lasted
* [EpisodeOfCare](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/episodeofcare.html): The provided date search value falls within the episode of care's period
* [FamilyMemberHistory](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/familymemberhistory.html): When history was recorded or last updated
* [Flag](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/flag.html): Time period when flag is active
* [Immunization](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/immunization.html): Vaccination  (non)-Administration Date
* [List](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/list.html): When the list was prepared
* [Observation](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/observation.html): Obtained date/time. If the obtained element is a period, a date that falls in the period
* [Procedure](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/procedure.html): When the procedure was performed
* [RiskAssessment](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/riskassessment.html): When was assessment made?
* [SupplyRequest](https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/supplyrequest.html): When the request was made
